<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note 1">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note 1.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Spach, 1839" authorityName="Spach" authorityYear="1839" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Yulania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Yulania" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Yulania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spach (
<bibRefCitation author="Spach, E" journalOrPublisher="1. Yunnan Science &amp; Technology Press, Kunming" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31485519" refId="B73" refString="Spach, E, 1839. Histoire Naturelle des Vegetaux. Phanerogames VII. Dicotyledones. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 1-538. [In French] https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31485519" title="Histoire Naturelle des Vegetaux. Phanerogames VII. Dicotyledones. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 1 - 538. [In French]" url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31485519" year="1839">Spach 1839</bibRefCitation>
) was resurrected in Flora of China (
<bibRefCitation author="Xia, NH" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="7 (Menispermaceae through Capparaceae). Science Press, Beijing and Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="48 - 91" publicationUrl="http://flora.huh.harvard.edu/china/mss/volume07/Magnoliaceae.pdf" refId="B84" refString="Xia, NH, Liu, YH [Law YW], Nooteboom, HP, 2008. Magnoliaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Hong, DY, Eds., Flora of China, Text Vol. 7 (Menispermaceae through Capparaceae). Science Press, Beijing and Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis: 48 - 91, http://flora.huh.harvard.edu/china/mss/volume07/Magnoliaceae.pdf" title="Magnoliaceae." url="http://flora.huh.harvard.edu/china/mss/volume07/Magnoliaceae.pdf" volumeTitle="Flora of China, Text Vol." year="2008">Xia et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), but there has not been universal acceptance of this in China, with 
<taxonomicName authority="Spach, 1839" authorityName="Spach" authorityYear="1839" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Yulania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="(Yulania)" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Yulania">Yulania</taxonomicName>
again recognised as a subgenus under 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Magnolia</taxonomicName>
(Ying et al. 2009, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, KM" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B86" refString="Yang, KM, Chen, XL, Gong, X, Wang, YL [Eds], 2016. Ex Situ Cultivated Flora of China : Magnoliaceae. Science Press, Beijing" title="Ex Situ Cultivated Flora of China: Magnoliaceae." year="2016">Yang et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note 2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note 2.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Spach, 1839" authorityName="Spach" authorityYear="1839" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Yulania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Yulania pilocarpa subsp. var. var. ellipticifolia" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pilocarpa" subSpecies="var." variety="ellipticifolia">Yulania pilocarpa var. ellipticifolia</taxonomicName>
is sufficiently distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="Y." lsidName="Y. pilocarpa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="pilocarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Y. pilocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to maintain its varietal status by the following features: indumentum of the branchlets (densely pubescent, later glabrous vs. glabrous [Law et al. 2004: 93]); the leaf shape (elliptical, rarely inverted-triangular vs. obovate to broadly obovate [Law et al. 2004]) and the shape and size of the inner 6 tepals (petaloid, 5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3.2 cm vs. nearly spathulate, 7-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 cm [Law et al. 2004]). Additionally, the two taxa are geographically isolated (central Henan Province vs. SE Hubei Province). The illustration of the leaves accompanying the original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Spach, 1839" authorityName="Spach" authorityYear="1839" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Yulania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Yulania pilocarpa subsp. var. var. ellipticifolia" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="pilocarpa" subSpecies="var." variety="ellipticifolia">Yulania pilocarpa var. ellipticifolia</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fu, DL" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Botanical Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="525 - 526" publicationUrl="http://bbr.nefu.edu.cn/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=412" refId="B31" refString="Fu, DL, Zhao, TB, Zhao, J, Zhao, DW, 2007. Two new varieties of Yulania Spach from Henan. Bulletin of Botanical Research 27 (5): 525 - 526, http://bbr.nefu.edu.cn/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=412" title="Two new varieties of Yulania Spach from Henan." url="http://bbr.nefu.edu.cn/CN/article/downloadArticleFile.do?attachType=PDF&amp;id=412" volume="27" year="2007">Fu et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
: fig.1D) shows them to be in stark contrast to the leaves of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. Z. Zhao &amp; Z. W. Xie" authorityYear="1987" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Magnolia pilocarpa" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilocarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Magnolia pilocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, YH (Law YW)" journalOrPublisher="Baitong Group, Beijing Science &amp; Technology Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B55" refString="Liu, YH (Law YW), Zeng, QW, Zhou, RZ, Xing, FW [Eds], 2004. Magnolias of China. Baitong Group, Beijing Science &amp; Technology Press, Beijing" title="Magnolias of China." year="2004">Liu et al. (2004</bibRefCitation>
: 93).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
